<h1>Govspeak help</h1>
<div>
  <h2>Style</h2>
  <p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/designprinciples/styleguide">View styleguide</a></p>
  <h2>Headings</h2>
<pre>## Top level heading - H2
### Second level heading - H3
#### Third level heading - H4

Don't use a single # - this is H1 and is for the title only

</pre>

  <h2>Internal links</h2>
  <p>Policies, publications, news, speeches, detailed guides etc. can be linked using URLs from within the admin interface</p>
  <pre>[link text](/government/admin/policies/3373 "Hover text goes here")</pre>

  <p>Series pages, topics, organisations, people, roles etc. should use public URLs from gov.uk</p>
  <pre>[link text](https://www.gov.uk/government/topics/climate-change "Hover text goes here")</pre>

  <h2>External links</h2>
  <p>Links with external URLs will automatically display as external links</p>
  <pre>[link text](http://www.example.com "Hover text goes here")</pre>

  <h2>Unordered List</h2>
  <pre>* item 1
* item 2
  * subitem
  * another subitem
(to indent add 2 spaces)</pre>
  <h2>Ordered List</h2>
  <pre>1. item 1
2. item 2
3. item 3
  * subitem
  * another subitem
(to indent add 2 spaces)</pre>
</div>

  <h2>Images</h2>
  <p>First upload your image(s), then:</p>
  <pre>!!<em>n</em></pre>
  <p>e.g. for the first image:</p>
  <pre>!!1</pre>

  <h2>Video links</h2>
  <p>Links to YouTube videos will automatically be displayed in an embedded media player.</p>
  <pre>[link text](youtube-video-url)</pre>
  <p>Use the title of the video for the "link text", e.g. :-</p>
  <pre>[The Queens Diamond Jubilee Concert](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OXHPWmnycno)</pre>

  <h2>Attachments</h2>
  <p><em>Not used on publications or consultations (attachments are placed automatically).</em></p>
  <p>First upload your attachment(s), then, to create an attachment callout box:</p>
  <pre>!@<em>n</em></pre>
  <p>Or, if you want to use a link to an attachment in a sentence or list:</p>
  <pre>[InlineAttachment:<em>n</em>]</pre>
  <p>e.g. for the first file:</p>
  <pre>!@1</pre>
  <p>or:</p>
  <pre>[InlineAttachment:1]</pre>


